President Biden visited the Lucy Evans Baylands Nature Interpretive Center in Palo Alto, California, to discuss climate resilience and investment in clean energy. He praised the efforts of local leaders and emphasized the importance of working together to combat climate change. The President announced the launch of the Climate Resilience Regional Challenge, which will provide $600 million to coastal and Great Lake communities for projects that protect against climate change impacts. He also announced a $2 billion investment by the Department of Energy to modernize the electric grid for climate resilience and the hosting of a White House summit later this year focused on climate resilience. President Biden expressed optimism about the future and called on Americans to work together to address the climate crisis. He also mentioned opposition from some Republicans in Congress but vowed to continue protecting climate provisions.